	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Class_hierarchy  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_hierarchy "/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_hierarchy">
A <b>Class_hierarchy</b> is a hierarchical relationship between two instances of <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/>.
<note>The <b>Class_hierarchy</b> is used to build up hierarchical structures of <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/> instances.</note>
		<example>With <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/>, part families such as screws can be classified. Additionally subclasses can be built and linked to the super-category screws, such as machine screw or self-tapping screw.</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Class_hierarchy   Attribute: super_class 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_hierarchy.super_class"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_hierarchy.super_class">
the higher level of <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/> in a <b>Class_hierarchy</b> that includes the sub class.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Class_hierarchy   Attribute: sub_class 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_hierarchy.sub_class"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_hierarchy.sub_class">
the lower level of <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/> in a <b>Class_hierarchy</b> that is included in the super class.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Class_with_attributes  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes">
A <b>Class_with_attributes</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="class:arm:Class_arm.Class"/> that may be defined with a set of valued parameters.
<example number="1">A standard type of screws can be classified according to its head type, its diameter and its length.</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Class_with_attributes  Attribute: version_id 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.version_id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.version_id">
the identification of a particular version of a <b>Class_with_attributes</b>. The value of the attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Class_with_attributes  Attribute: used_classification_system 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.used_classification_system"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.used_classification_system">
<p>the <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system"/> that contains the information about the definition of the classification and how to interpret the name of the <b>Class_with_attributes</b>. 
The value of the attribute need not be specified.</p>

<example number="2">
			<p>For facilitating an effective part retrieval for slotted screws, several instances of <b>Class_with_attributes</b> may be defined to classify screws: 
</p>
			<ul>
				<li>A <b>Class_with_attributes</b> *1 with description 'slotted screws' and the following three subclasses 
</li>
				<li>A <b>Class_with_attributes</b> *2 with description 'slotted cheese head screws - product grade A', 
</li>
				<li>A <b>Class_with_attributes</b> *3 with description 'slotted pan head screws - product grade A', and 
</li>
				<li>A <b>Class_with_attributes</b> *4 with description 'slotted countersunk flat head screws - product grade A'.
</li>
			</ul>
			<p> 
Each of these instances is based on a <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system"/> that further defines where the definition of the classification comes from. 
For *1, this is a company internal <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system"/> for 'screw classes'. 
For the other instances, these are <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system"/> instances identifying ISO standards, 
namely for *2 'ISO 1207', for *3 'ISO 1580', and for *4 'ISO 2009'. 
</p>
		</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Class_with_attributes  Attribute: characterization_attributes 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.characterization_attributes"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes.characterization_attributes">
<p>the <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute"/> instances that characterize the <b>Class_with_attributes</b>.</p>
<example number="3">
According to ISO 1207, the <b>Class_with_attributes</b> *2 has the attributes *11 with id 'd' and name 'thread', 
*12 with id 'l' and name 'nominal length', *13 with id 'mechanical properties' and name 'property class', and so on. 
The possible values 'M1.6', 'M2', ..., 'M10' for <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute"/> *11 may be defined as instances of a subtype of <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Measure_item"/>. 
The thread class name, 'M1.6', 'M2', ..., is represented within the name attribute of the referenced instances of <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Measure_item"/>. 
</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: External_class_with_attributes  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.External_class_with_attributes"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.External_class_with_attributes">
An <b>External_class_with_attributes</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/> that is defined in an external library.
<example>
The classification may be defined in an ISO 13584 compliant library (PLIB). 
In this case, the <b>External_class_with_attributes</b> references as a classification source a <express_ref linkend="plib_class_reference:arm:Plib_class_reference_arm.Plib_class_reference"/> that has an id corresponding to the class BSU, that is a world wide unique identification of that class as defined according to ISO 13584-42.
</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: External_class_with_attributes  Attribute: source 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.External_class_with_attributes.source"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.External_class_with_attributes.source">
the <express_ref linkend="plib_class_reference:arm:Plib_class_reference_arm.Plib_class_reference"/> or <express_ref linkend="external_class:arm:External_class_arm.External_class"/> that identifies the external specification of the <b>External_class_with_attributes</b>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_association  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association">
A <b>Classification_association</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="classification_assignment:arm:Classification_assignment_arm.Classification_assignment"/> that associates a <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/> with product or activity data.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_association  Attribute: assigned_class
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.assigned_grouping"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.assigned_class">
the <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/> instance that provides classification information.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_association  Attribute: definitional 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.definitional"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.definitional">
a logical value that specifies whether a <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/> serves as definition of the classified element.
A value of 'true' indicates that the <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/> is definitional.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_association  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.wr:WR1">
When definitional is true, the <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/> shall be assigned to instances of type <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.definable_objects"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_association  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_association.wr:WR2">
Only items of types listed in <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.classified_element_select"/> shall be referred to by a <b>Classification_association</b>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute">
A <b>Classification_attribute</b> is a characteristic of a <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/>.
A set of values may precise the allowed values of that characteristic.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  Attribute: id 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.id">
the identifier of the <b>Classification_attribute</b>.
This identifier shall be unique within the scope of the associated <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.name">
<p>the word or group of words by which the <b>Classification_attribute</b> is referred to. 
The value of the attribute need not be specified.</p>
<example>'length', 'width', or 'radius' are examples for the name of a <b>Classification_attribute</b>.</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.description">
a text that provides additional information about the <b>Classification_attribute</b>. The value of the attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  Attribute: allowed_values 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.allowed_values"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.allowed_values">
<p>the set of instances of <express_ref linkend="Measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Measure_item"/> that specify the allowed values of the <b>Classification_attribute</b>. 
The value of the attribute need not be specified.</p>
<note>The values may be specified as single values or value ranges.</note>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_attribute  Attribute: characterized_class 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.characterized_class"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_attribute.characterized_class">
the <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Class_with_attributes"/> of which the <b>Classification_attribute</b> defines a characteristic.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_arm  Entity: Classification_system  
   <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:arm:Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_arm.Classification_system">
A <b>Classification_system</b> is a schema defining classifications of product or activity data.
<example>
A dictionary collecting the conventional definitions of technical properties is an example of <b>Classification_system</b>.
</example>
	</ext_description>
